Tannenberg: Stalluponen

August 17, 1914

The opening battle between Russian and German forces during WWI began at Stalluponen, just inside German Eastern Prussia.  With surprising speed, Russia concentrated her regular army for an attack against Germany while mobilization was underway.  Within two weeks of the declaration of hostilities, Russia was ready to wage an offensive campaign against Germany - surpassing the German estimate by 4 weeks.

General Epanchin's III Corps, of the 1st Russian Army (Rennekampf) reached the city of Stalluponen and engaged General von Francois' I Corps of the 8th Army (von Prittwitz).

